(486, 8149, 19, 0, '19', 'She/ Her', 'Student', NULL, 'Isdi', 'Mom', 'null', '', '', '', '4', '4', '4', NULL, '5', 0, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'no_book', NULL, 'Ritu Bhate', '9589483129', 'None diagnosed ', 'Anxiety, attacks, overthinking ', 'no', 'no', '', '-', 'agree', 'agree', NULL, '2024-11-25', '1. Follow up on previously suggested techniques\r\n2. Reflection Self-growth \r\n3. Setting new goals for maintaining wellbeing ', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-05-09 04:48:25', '2024-05-09 04:48:25'),
(487, 8149, 19, 0, '19', 'She/ Her', 'Student', NULL, 'Isdi', 'Mom', 'null', '', '', '', '4', '4', '4', NULL, '5', 0, '2024-05-09', '11:30am-12:15pm', 'https://meet.google.com/uxb-rrei-min?authuser=0', 'It was really good, comforting and helpful ', '.', 'Yes', '4', '4', '5', '5', 'completed', NULL, 'Ritu Bhate', '9589483129', 'None diagnosed ', 'Anxiety, attacks, overthinking ', 'no', 'no', '', '-', 'agree', 'agree', 'Client’s mother had approached us to provide therapy sessions to her daughter. She mentioned to the team that her daughter had reported indications towards harming herself. None of this information was reported by the client in the first session.\r\n\r\nClient reported experiencing the following symptoms:\r\nFeeling panicky, on the edge, pukish, breathlessness, fatigue\r\nFrequent Crying bouts stemming from what ifs\r\nPreoccupation with “worst case scenario”\r\nMuscle stiffness\r\n\r\nPersonal + Family history:\r\nMarital discord of Parents\r\nAbusive father + infidelity\r\nFather had multiple partners & wives\r\n\r\nWork done:\r\nUnderstanding the case & the patterns\r\nIdentified adaptations of Childhood trauma\r\nOvergeneralization of childhood trauma\r\nCognitive distortions: Overgeneralization, Negative filter\r\nPsycho education on: Survival mode+ Nervous system+ deep breathing\r\nReal v/s perceived threats\r\n', '2024-11-25', '1. Follow up on previously suggested techniques\r\n2. Reflection Self-growth \r\n3. Setting new goals for maintaining wellbeing ', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-05-09 04:48:53', '2024-05-09 04:50:04'),
(491, 8212, 19, 0, '18', 'He/him', 'Dropper', NULL, 'Dropper', 'Puneet sharma', 'null', '', '', '', '1', '1', '1', NULL, '1', 0, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'no_book', NULL, 'Dinesh katare', '9425496757', 'Hypothyroidism, Depression, anxiety, mania panic attacks.', 'Depression anxiety and childhood trauma', 'ocassional', 'yes', '', 'Not comfortable right now ', 'agree', 'agree', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'psy_shortnote', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-05-10 09:35:33', '2024-05-10 09:35:33'),
(492, 5028, 19, 0, '24', 'Khush', 'Student', NULL, 'Germany ', 'Shruti', 'null', '', '', '', '4', '4', '4', NULL, '4', 0, '2024-05-13', '10:45am-11:30am', '', 'Can’t express in words. Just amazing', 'No', 'Yes', '5', '5', '5', '5', 'completed', NULL, 'Khushdeep kumar', '9872612342', 'No', 'Obsession with a person', 'no', 'no', '', 'For now things are really good.', 'agree', 'agree', 'Client has reported further improvement in well-being. \r\n\r\nWork done:\r\nSocial Anxiety- Opposite action urge\r\nCognitive restructuring for maladaptive thought \"wo meri hai\" stemming from past relationship + building acceptance\r\nDifferentiating helpful from unhelpful thoughts of Anxiety\r\nImportance of Rest and comfort zone\r\nCatastrophising thoughts leading to Anxiety\r\n ', '2024-11-25', '1. Follow up - Present status and follow up on the tips suggested earlier\r\n2. Mindfulness based relaxation \r\n', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-05-10 10:00:15', '2024-05-10 10:01:02'),
(499, 8259, 13, 31, '51', 'test', '514514', NULL, 'asedasew', 'asdfdasf', 'null', '', '', '', '1', '1', '1', NULL, '1', 0, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'no_book', NULL, 'das', '5464949595', 'asddaswdfawed', 'wfawfd', 'no', 'no', 'wefdewefwqfq', 'efdsdf', 'agree', 'agree', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'psy_shortnote', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-05-12 08:17:37', '2024-05-12 08:17:37'),
(516, 8363, 19, 0, '25', 'she/her', 'Marketing Manager', NULL, 'Simpl', 'NA', 'null', '', '', '', '1', '3', '2', NULL, '1', 0, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'no_book', NULL, 'Siddharth Maniar', '7045524155', 'NA', 'Sadness, Anxiety', 'ocassional', 'yes', '', 'NA', 'agree', 'agree', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'psy_shortnote', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-05-15 18:29:47', '2024-05-15 18:29:47'),
(517, 8149, 19, 0, '19', 'She/ her', 'Student ', NULL, 'ISDI', 'Mom', 'null', '', '', '', '4', '5', '4', NULL, '5', 0, '2024-05-16', '10:45am-11:30am', 'https://meet.google.com/pqx-iwpk-dhw?authuser=0', 'Really good', '.', 'Yes', '3', '4', '5', '5', 'completed', NULL, 'Ritu Bhate', '9589483129', 'Nil', 'Anxiety, attacks, overthinking ', 'no', 'no', '', '-', 'agree', 'agree', 'Client reported improvement in her symptoms in the past week, is able to focus on & prioritize Self care, leisure & hobbies. \r\nShe reported having difficulties with Uncertainty, change of plans & minor inconveniences leading to catastrophic emotions & outbursts. She then associates these inconveniences with childhood trauma (overgeneralization) and experiences trust issues.\r\nThinking style is on the extremes- “My partner is late, he is cheating on me”, “My partner supported me, he’s nice & kind, I’m leading to problems in his life”\r\nMentioned mismatch of love- languages: Client requires verbal reassurances, partner does acts of service\r\nHypervigilance is heightened\r\n\r\nWork done:\r\nIdentified distortions: Negative filter, All or none, Overgeneralization, Jumping to conclusions, Catasrophizing, Personalisation & blame\r\nCognitive restructuring through socratic questioning & thought challenging by checking validity of the thoughts\r\nPsycho- education on: Cognitive flexibility & how to increase it\r\nPsycho- education: Real v/s perceived threats\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2024-11-25', '1. Follow up on previously suggested techniques\r\n2. Reflection Self-growth \r\n3. Setting new goals for maintaining wellbeing ', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-05-15 21:11:40', '2024-05-15 21:14:20'),
(522, 8410, 19, 0, '32', 'Her', 'Service', NULL, 'HCL', 'NA', 'null', '', '', '', '2', '2', '2', NULL, '1', 0, '2024-05-17', '12:15pm-1:00pm', 'https://meet.google.com/ekr-bqyp-ums?authuser=0', 'Nice , she was patient to listen everything ', 'Nothing as of now ', 'Yes', '3', '1', '4', '4', 'completed', NULL, 'Ankit Sadani', '9922282215', 'NO', 'not feeling good about self', 'no', 'yes', '', 'NO', 'agree', 'agree', 'Client reported experiencing symptoms of anxiety. She mentioned being an extravert & further reported relocating back to Indore has led to to losing her old connection in friendships, WFH since last 4.5yrs have exacerbated symptoms of anxiety including increased anger outbursts, feelings of helplessness, over-control, heightened what ifs, increased day to day fears, frustration, Personalization and low confidence\r\n\r\nWork done:\r\nAnalysed patterns of Anxiety\r\nProblems with control & uncertainty\r\nOvergeneralization of past trauma\r\nPessimistic lens of viewing the world\r\nDay to day Fears\r\n\r\nTherapeutic plan: CBT\r\n', '2025-03-22', 'Goals for next session:\r\n\r\n1.  Reframing the \'What if\' scenarios. \r\n2. Focusing on Guilt free planning/scheduling\r\n3. Breaking free from the thought loop\r\n4. Follow up on previous goals', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-05-17 05:45:57', '2024-05-17 05:48:49'),
(528, 8149, 19, 0, '19', 'She/her', 'Student', NULL, 'ISDI', 'Mom', 'null', '', '', '', '2', '4', '3', NULL, '4', 0, '2024-05-22', '10:45am-11:30am', 'https://meet.google.com/ece-ycan-jzr?authuser=0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, 'Ritu Bhate', '9589483129', '-', 'Anxiety, overthinking ', 'no', 'no', '', '.', 'agree', 'agree', 'Discussed about personal triggers & how the present relationship is not triggering in itself but triggers because of Over generalization.\r\nDiscussed about why she’s getting more triggered being in a relationship\r\nProblems with uncertainty & change of plans were discussed and Psycho education was provided about childhood trauma, perceived threats & trauma adaptations\r\nWorked on Cognitive flexibility\r\nIdentified triggers and following thoughts, emotions & behaviors\r\n\r\n', '2024-11-25', '1. Follow up on previously suggested techniques\r\n2. Reflection Self-growth \r\n3. Setting new goals for maintaining wellbeing ', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-05-22 02:29:34', '2024-05-22 02:30:23'),
(532, 9489, 19, 0, '22', 'He/him ', 'Engineer ', NULL, 'Armed forces ', 'Referred by duty Medic (unsure of name)', 'null', '', '', '', '4', '3', '2', NULL, '4', 0, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'no_book', NULL, 'Andrew Lewis', '07714 0848', 'None. ', 'Anxiety. Overthinking, racing thoughts.', 'no', 'no', '', 'It’s something I’ve always struggled with and it’s not getting any better. I just could do with the ‘tools’ to help cope with the condition and self-help where I can. ', 'agree', 'agree', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'psy_shortnote', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-06-09 14:24:49', '2024-06-09 14:24:49'),
