(537, 8410, 19, 0, '32', 'Her', 'Service', NULL, 'Hcl', '', 'null', '', '', '', '2', '4', '2', NULL, '2', 0, '2024-06-29', '10:45am-11:30am', 'https://meet.google.com/koa-uvkh-qxv?authuser=0', 'Very nice', 'None', 'Yes', '3', '3', '4', '4', 'completed', NULL, 'Ankit', '9922282215', 'No', 'No self confidence ', 'no', 'yes', '', 'I already had a session', 'agree', 'agree', 'Client mentioned her everyday negative thoughts, out of which the most distressing is “What if a close one dies”, this thought is prevalent & causes significant amount of distress to the client. Other thoughts include “Bought a new car, what if I have an accident”, “I’ve had a miscarriage before, what if I’m never able to become a mother” etc.\r\nClient experiences day to day anxiety, is overly focused on the worst case scenario and negative thought patterns include: over- generalizing, catastrophising, negative filter\r\n\r\nWork done:\r\nAddressed fears \r\nFears within fears\r\nAddressed her cycle of negative thoughts: having a negative thought, fear that the universe will hear and manifest it- leads to suppressing the thought & emotions\r\nPsycho educated about Suppression\r\nAddressed fear of uncertainty\r\nHer cycle: Fear of uncertainty- leads to anticipating the worst case scenario- leads to feeling helpless & incapable of dealing with the situation- leads to emotional breakdowns or avoiding the situations altogether.\r\nAddressed Surviving v/s living\r\nIntroduction to Process work\r\nIdentifying everyday Real v/s perceived threat (Homework)\r\nGratitude practice- 3 good things about my day (Homework)\r\n\r\n', '2025-03-22', 'Goals for next session:\r\n\r\n1.  Reframing the \'What if\' scenarios. \r\n2. Focusing on Guilt free planning/scheduling\r\n3. Breaking free from the thought loop\r\n4. Follow up on previous goals', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-06-27 15:44:25', '2024-06-27 15:52:38'),
(553, 8410, 19, 0, '32', 'Her', 'Service', NULL, 'HCL', 'NA', 'null', '', '', 'null', '2', '2', '2', NULL, '2', 0, '2024-08-07', '12:15pm-1:00pm', 'https://meet.google.com/koa-uvkh-qxv?authuser=0', 'Very nice', 'Nothing as of now', 'Yes', '3', '2', '4', '4', 'completed', NULL, 'Ankit', '9922282215', 'No', 'No self confidence ', 'no', 'yes', '', 'I already had a session', 'agree', 'agree', 'Identified the root of catastrophic fears (what if people close to me die)\r\nIdentified family history of Anxiety\r\nIdentified childhood patterns\r\nIdentified dysfunctional thoughts “People dont want to spend time with a sad/ dull person”, “If I’m too sad around my husband, he will lose interest in me”, “There is something wrong with me”, \r\nIdentified low self esteem \r\nWorked with: Catastrophizing\r\nIdentified Self critical tone, perfectionism & lack of Self forgiveness patterns \r\nAddressed: Fear of disappointing others, Fear of failure, Fear of making mistakes\r\nDifficulty writing fears- fearing they will manifest\r\n', '2025-03-22', 'Goals for next session:\r\n\r\n1.  Reframing the \'What if\' scenarios. \r\n2. Focusing on Guilt free planning/scheduling\r\n3. Breaking free from the thought loop\r\n4. Follow up on previous goals', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-08-07 06:09:23', '2024-08-07 06:09:23'),
