(705, 1, 19, 0, '32', NULL, NULL, 'demo', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '1', '1', '1', NULL, '1', 0, '2024-08-24', '10:00am-10:45am', 'https://meet.google.com/jnr-krzu-vfa?authuser=0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, 'jaidip', '1234567890', 'demo', 'demo', 'no', 'no', '', 'demo', 'agree', 'agree', 'Client notes:\r\n\r\nClient is a 46 year old male, unmarried, belonging to high socio-economic status.\r\nHis chief complaints were: \r\n“Fear of losing job” by being falsely accused by a woman\r\n“Office politics” on being falsely accused around harassment\r\nStress, overthinking leading to sleep deprivation, social withdrawal, “being affected” by everyday negative thoughts around points 1 & 2\r\n\r\nPast history: \r\nClients has a past history of multiple trauma events around “being falsely accused” of harassing women, followed by filing of legal cases & consequently losing the job\r\nClient found himself jobless for 7-8 years in Singapore because of these events and was impacted by them\r\nBroken Engagement\r\nAll the above- mentioned incidences have formed a negative impact and bias towards women leading to fearing them\r\n\r\nWork done:\r\nExplored & identified patterns of trauma & its adaptations\r\nIdentified threat perception\r\nIdentified Stressors\r\nDiscussed the trauma adaptation with client\r\nPsycho educated about trauma, trauma adaptation, over- generalization, nervous system \r\nPracticed deep breathing within the session for nervous system regulation\r\n\r\n', '2024-11-26', '1. Follow up on previously set goals \r\n2. Adaption with difficult thoughts and relaxation\r\n3. Setting new goals based on current status ', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-08-20 15:55:18', '2024-08-20 16:05:10'),
(711, 10825, 19, 0, '44', NULL, NULL, 'She', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '1', '1', '1', NULL, '1', 0, '2024-08-23', '5:15pm-6:00pm', 'https://meet.google.com/bwq-fiev-wfv?authuser=0', 'Good', 'It was introductory session. Need insights into moving forward', 'yes', '4', '3', '4', '4', 'completed', NULL, 'Geetika Garg', '8178451814', 'Chronic Depression, Migraine, Vertigo', 'Depression', 'no', 'yes', '', 'Struggling to get out of bed, indulge in hobbies or do anything for myself.', 'agree', 'agree', 'Client is a 44 year old married female, belonging to high socio- economic status. She’s currently a home-maker & a visiting faculty at manipal university\r\nClient has reportedly visited multiple mental health professionals in the past including a Psychiatrist, psychologist & couple counselor. The following diagnosis were reported from previous professional: Bipolar disorder, Depression\r\n\r\nChief complaints were as follows:\r\nMarital discord due to “husband having enmeshed boundaries with his narcissistic mother”\r\nDisruption in married life due to interference of mother in law\r\n\r\nGoal: Client mentioned that she has worked enough times on the marriage and she is not willing to work on her marriage anymore. She wants to focus on “Self development, become happy, having a social circle and fully functioning individually”\r\n\r\nPlan of action:\r\nFormal diagnosis by a clinical psychologist\r\nReferral to the right professional\r\n\r\n', '2024-11-26', '1. Follow up on the techniques suggested previously and their impact.\r\n2. Management of difficult thoughts\r\n3. Management of Grief', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-08-23 11:00:38', '2024-08-23 11:03:49'),
(740, 8410, 19, 0, '32', 'Her', 'Service', 'Her', 'HCL', '', '', '', '', '', '2', '4', '1', NULL, '2', 0, '2024-09-13', '4:00pm-4:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/uzz-qqif-qnu', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, 'Ankit', '9922282215', 'No', 'Fears and negativity ', 'no', 'yes', '', 'Already had sessions just want to continue', 'agree', 'agree', '- Follow up on the previous interventions: \nFollowed Gratitude exercise for 1 week, then left. \n(Felt good and slighlty positive).\n\n- Presenting Complaints: \n1. Fear of losing loved ones. \n2. Negative thoughts related to something awful that might happen (content based on news/tv/phone).\n3. Job insecurity (technology she works in might not be required in the future/options for work opportunity in future).\n4. Superstitious based on past beliefs. \n5. Lack of awareness on scheduling the daily/weekly routine. \n6. Lack of interest in socializing.\n\n- Chief Complaints: \n1. Anxiety \n2. Stress related to self and concerns for family members\n3. Over-thinking\n4. Lack of social support\n5. Sleep related concerns (Sleep duration, daytime dysfunction and frequent dreams)\n6. Frequent feelings of irritation\n7. Lack of Self confidence and belief in self. \n\n- Assessments: \n1. GAD-7: Severe Anxiety (19/21)\n2. PSS: High Percieved Stress (27/40)\n\n- Current Interventions Suggested: \n1. Positive Affirmations: In context to positive self-talk, in order to boost her self-esteem.\n2. Jacobson\'s Progressive Muscle Relaxation: To be practiced towards night while lying down on the bed, in order to release any kind of physical tension, reduce the levels of restlessness and pressure, and reduce the frequency of dreams.\n3. Distraction Techniques: Interest based activities to be practiced at the time of negative thoughts being experienced by her. So that, she can focus on something productive and reduce the impact of the thought. \n\n*Quick fix relaxation techniques: \n1. Box breathing: To be practiced every morning (3-5 time), in order and at the time of feelings of restlessness and overwhelmingness. \n2. Physical grounding: Place the bare feet on ground and lying down straight on the ground/floor in order to distract the mind and fade away the thoughts. \n3. Temperature change: Twice or thrice every week dip the feet in lukewarm water and wash the face and feet with cold/normal water before going to bed. \n\n- Positive aspects/Strengths of the client: \n1. Insightful\n2. Cooperative and Understanding\n3. Good self control \n4. Takes efforts', '2025-03-22', 'Goals for next session:\r\n\r\n1.  Reframing the \'What if\' scenarios. \r\n2. Focusing on Guilt free planning/scheduling\r\n3. Breaking free from the thought loop\r\n4. Follow up on previous goals', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-09-13 01:12:53', '2024-09-13 01:14:35'),
