(755, 10825, 19, 0, '44', 'She', 'Housewife', 'She', 'NA', '', '', '', '', '', '1', '1', '1', NULL, '1', 0, '2024-09-25', '7:00pm-7:45pm', 'Session with Mrs. Geetika Garg  Wednesday, September 25 · 7:00 – 8:00pm Time zone: Asia/Kolkata Google Meet joining info Video call link: https://meet.google.com/qvi-kvec-mtv Or dial: ‪(US) +1 636-707-2171‬ PIN: ‪661 727 492‬# More phone numbers: https://tel.meet/qvi-kvec-mtv?pin=6714968224398', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, 'Amit Garg', '9315896912', 'Mo', 'Chronic Depression', 'ocassional', 'yes', '', 'already shared', 'agree', 'agree', '# Previous Consultations/Hospitalizations: Previously consulted Psychologists (Couple counsellor - twice and Individual - Once). \r\n# Provisional Diagnosis: Bipolar Personality \r\n# Duration of consultation: Does not remember specifically (1 year combined). \r\n# Previous complains: Misunderstandings and conflicts with mother in law, marital conflicts and adjustment issues with husband and in-laws. \r\n# Any other medical conditions: Heart related challenges.  \r\n# History of medications: Heart issues (April-June 2024 ) and Anti-depressants (July 2024) - stopped on her own due to enhanced drowsiness and lack of willingness. \r\n# Presenting Complaints: 1. Lack of self compassion 2. Lack of self motivation 3. Lack of willingness to work on the marriage 4. Adjustment and communication issues with husband 5. Adjustment and trust issues with mother-in-law 6. Concerns related to children and their mental health 7. Lost her mother (few months back)\r\n# Chief Complaints: 1. Depressive symptoms 2. Stress related to marriage 3. Low self esteem 4. Negative thoughts and self talk 5. Overthinking 6. Insecurity related to doubts on husband \r\n# Current Interventions Suggested: \r\n1. Sleep hygiene: Including self soothing activites in order to promote acceptance and self compassion. \r\n2. Progressive Muscle Relaxtion: Reduce anxiety, stress and overthinking enhancing sense of relaxation. \r\n3. Letter to Self: To help understand the self better and focus on the things that she really wants. \r\n(including a focus on strengths, journey in past 2-3 months and acknowledging the efforts she has taken to overcome that). \r\n# Strengths of the client: 1. Insightful 2. Willing 3. Courageous 4. Diligent. ', '2024-11-26', '1. Follow up on the techniques suggested previously and their impact.\r\n2. Management of difficult thoughts\r\n3. Management of Grief', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-09-25 11:11:50', '2024-09-25 11:13:36'),
(756, 10857, 19, 0, '26', 'MS.', 'Working as Market Research Analyst', 'MS.', 'LSC', 'Sneh Nigam Ma\'am', '', '', '', '', '3', '3', '3', NULL, '3', 0, '2024-09-28', '5:00pm-5:45pm', 'First Consultation call - Ms. Surbhi Gupta Saturday, September 28 · 5:00 – 6:00pm Time zone: Asia/Kolkata Google Meet joining info Video call link: https://meet.google.com/mfy-ipdd-adz Or dial: ‪(US) +1 423-712-0178‬ PIN: ‪421 030 228‬# More phone numbers: https://tel.meet/mfy-ipdd-adz?pin=8699546949639', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, 'Mahima Gupta', '9713269660', 'PCOD', 'No', 'no', 'no', '', 'I wanted to share about my breakup and the things going on inside my head. I have been trying for a long and have not been able to get over him.', 'agree', 'agree', '#Demographics: From Hoshangabad, education in Bhopal&Gandhinagar, Was living in Pune from last 3.5 years as a working professional, recently switched to Mumbai (1 month). \r\n#Previous consultations/History of medications: None. \r\n#Work: IT Company (Market Researcher), timings: 10 AM to 8 PM (30 minutes travelling). \r\n#Present Compaints: 1. Adjustment with the new place and culture 2. Adjustment with new work environment and culture 3. Lack of social support 4. Not interested in carrying out the routine activitities 5. Difficulty accepting self 6. Difficulty coping up with breakup (7-8 months back).\r\n#Chief Complaints: 1. Depression 2. Stress due to transition 3. Loneliness 4. Lack of Self-compassion 5. Difficult/Negative thoughts 6. Lack of scheduling/prioritization. \r\n#Current Interventions Suggested: 1. Sleep hygiene and Self soothing activitites 2. Distraction Techniques 3. Tips for socializing with long distance friends 4. ABC Technique for time managment and scheduling 5. Positive Affirmations\r\n#Strengths of the client: 1. Insightful 2. Straight forward 3. Ability to set boundaries 4. Clear communication 5. Willing to take efforts. ', '2024-11-25', '1. Maintenance of previous goals\r\n2. Cognitive Restructuring - Shifting focus from negative to positive thought process. \r\n3. Anxiety Management and maintenance \r\n4. Art of setting Boundaries', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-09-27 10:54:23', '2024-09-27 11:05:46'),
