(798, 449, 19, 0, '24', 'Ravi', 'working professional', 'Ravi', 'Amity', '', '', '', '', '', '5', '5', '5', NULL, '5', 0, '2024-11-23', '7:00pm-7:45pm', ' https://meet.google.com/ecp-hqbs-hey ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, 'Ravi Saini', '8923655029', 'none', 'none', 'ocassional', 'no', '', 'none', 'agree', 'agree', 'Demographic details: Government servant, lives with younger brother. \r\nChief complaints: Lack of clarity, anxiety, overthinking, fear of death, lack of time management and interest in daily activiites, conflicts with partner. \r\nInterventions shared: JPMR, sleep hygiene and self-soothing activities, thought journaling, 2-minute action plan and positive affirmations. ', '2024-12-18', NULL, 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-11-23 12:50:15', '2024-11-23 12:52:14'),
(802, 10882, 19, 0, '29', 'Kamlesh Rabde', 'Govt servant ', 'Kamlesh Rabde', 'Labour Department Bhopal', 'Mayank Agarwal', '', '', '', '', '3', '3', '3', NULL, '1', 0, '2024-12-04', '9:00pm-9:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/cuk-ynkh-spa ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, 'Mayank Agarwal', '9826508505', 'GERD', 'Death thoughts, sleeplessness , rapid heartbeats', 'no', 'no', '', '1. Constant rapid heartbeats\r\n2.  Sleeplessness\r\n3. Running way from people\r\n4. Constant thoughts running\r\n5. Does not feel like talking to anybody\r\n6. Always want to be alone\r\n7. Frequent death thoughts, suicidal thoughts\r\n8. Not having proper meal', 'agree', 'agree', 'Family business - travel agent \r\nchief complaints: frequent mood swings, fear of failure, self doubts and low self esteem, lives with his wife (marriage conflicts since last 3 years)\r\nInterventions discussed: Negative thought restructuring, Progressive muscle relaxation, box breathing, positive self-talk and affirmations, working on the attachment style analysis in order to understand work with the communication style. ', '2024-12-20', 'Goals decided for this call:\r\n\r\n1. Identifying the pattern of unhealthy thoughts\r\n2. Reframing unhealthy thoughts with healhty ones\r\n3. Mood management  ', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2024-12-04 12:53:46', '2024-12-04 13:05:27'),
(839, 10891, 19, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', '2', '2', '2', NULL, '2', 0, '2025-01-16', '02:00pm-02:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/gaj-sbpy-pag ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'agree', 'agree', '#Present Complaints: 1. Fear of dying 2. Fear of Future (Avoids conversation related to it) 3. Afraid of planning things (be it big or small) 4. Difficulty in visualizing \'how things will go!\' 5. Fear of change/Uncertainity 6. Difficulty in expressing self \n#Chief Complaints: 1. Anxiety 2. Irritation 3. Occassional outbursts (Emotional and anger) 4. Fear of Uncertainity 5. Unresolved grief from childhood 6. Contradicting fears of planning kids and biologically time is  passing for the wife\n#Intervention Plan: 1. Box breathing 2. EMDR Guided meditation 3. Letter to Self (Unresolved concerns).\n#Strengths of the client: 1. Insightful 2. \'Go with the Flow\' attitude - staying in present 3. Caring and concerned for wife and family 4. Gentle and supportive for wife/mother and even others. ', '2025-02-05', '1. Follow up on previous goals.\r\n2. Assessments to get a better insight into the present challenges. \r\n3. Diving deeper into the challenges and recognising the patterns. \r\n4. Building skills for Emotional expression. ', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 12, '', NULL, 0, '2025-01-10 04:10:28', '2025-01-15 03:31:48'),
(873, 8410, 19, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', '3', '5', '2', NULL, '2', 0, '2025-03-01', '1:00pm-1:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/bax-csep-ych ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'agree', 'agree', '#Follow up on previous goals: 1. Followed the JPMR for a week and felt realy relaxed. She was successfully able to break free from overthinking and get some sleep. 2. Left after that, as she got busy with wedding in the family. #Chief Complaints: 1. Felling Low 2. Frequent irritation 3. Feelings of loneliness 4. Emotional exhaustion 5. Unwillingness to express herself completely 6. Stress and signs of mild depression #Major triggers: 1. Emotional unavailibility of husband 2. Having no social life 3. Mild works stress 4. Frequent work related travel of husband 5. Inability to spend quality time together #Intervention suggested: 1. Previous techniques reshared to develop relaxation again 2. Suggested to ways to develop a habit and self-check ins 3. Framework (worksheet) in order to identify the negative thought loop. #Major strengths of the client: 1. Insightful 2. Understanding 3. Willing to work upon herself 4. Open to changes ', '2025-03-22', 'Goals for next session:\r\n\r\n1.  Reframing the \'What if\' scenarios. \r\n2. Focusing on Guilt free planning/scheduling\r\n3. Breaking free from the thought loop\r\n4. Follow up on previous goals', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 1, '{\"1\":{\"question\":\"What is your primary reason for seeking therapy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Any other\",\"input\":\"Anxiety\"}]},\"2\":{\"question\":\"How often do you experience feelings of sadness or loneliness?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Almost always\"}]},\"3\":{\"question\":\"How comfortable are you with sharing personal experiences?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Very comfortable\"}]},\"4\":{\"question\":\"Do you feel supported by your friends and family?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Somewhat supported\"}]},\"5\":{\"question\":\"What is your biggest source of stress?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Family\"},{\"option\":\"Work\"},{\"option\":\"Relationships\"},{\"option\":\"Financial issues\"}]},\"6\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel overwhelmed by responsibilities?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Almost always\"}]},\"7\":{\"question\":\"How would you describe your self-esteem?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Low\"}]},\"8\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel unmotivated or lacking energy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Almost always\"}]},\"9\":{\"question\":\"How well do you handle setbacks?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Somewhat well\"}]},\"10\":{\"question\":\"Are you open to exploring your past experiences in therapy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Very open\"}]}}', NULL, 0, '2025-03-01 03:12:12', '2025-03-01 03:12:12'),
(878, 10899, 19, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', '1', '2', '2', NULL, '2', 0, '2025-03-07', '8:00pm-8:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/jhg-nefp-kyt', 'It was good,but last week was very bad,even had serious suicidal thoughts,felt very low ', 'I felt low very often,isolated myself ', 'Yes I was able to open up to psychologist ', '2', '2', '2', '2', 'completed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'agree', 'agree', '#Basic Details: Student - 3rd yea MBBS, lives in hostel (single room), nuclear family (parents and elder sister, MBBS student as well). #Love interest: He was in a 3 year long relationship with a boy he met in Kota (his professor there). They have 5 years age gap and met only 4 times in proximity after coming in a long distance relationship from last 2 years.  Recently they broke up as his partner claimed that he is bisexual and now his parents are pressurising him for marriage. He is unwilling to have any kind of contact with the client. The client is unable to accept the fact and is facing mental as well as emotional challenges due to this. #Presenting Complaints: 1. Lack of acceptance 2. Low self-worth 3. Low Self-confidence 4. Isolation 5. Lack of interest in daily activities 6. Stage 1 of grief cycle - Denial 7. Impact on studies #Chief Complaints: 1. Depression 2. Frequent irritation 3. Loss of appetite (weight loss: 8 kgs in 1 month) 4. Sleep issues (Latency period very long) 5. Lack of motivation 6. Disturbed routine 7. Lack of concentration 8. Anxiety 9. Self-doubt (breakup and sexual identity) #Medical History: Visitng Psychiatrist in Bhopal (Dr. Shivam Bhandari). Currently on medications (Anti-depressants) since 13th February.  #Intervention: 1. JPMR 2. Sleep hygiene 3. Distraction techniques 4. Physical grounding 5. Thought identification.  ', '2025-04-01', '1. Follow up on the previous goals. \r\n2. Practicing Self-compassion.\r\n3. Focusing on Self. ', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 28, '{\"1\":{\"question\":\"What brings you to therapy? (Select all that apply)\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Stress or anxiety\"},{\"option\":\"Depression or sadness\"},{\"option\":\"Relationship issues\"},{\"option\":\"Trauma or past experiences\"},{\"option\":\"Low self-esteem or confidence\"},{\"option\":\"Overthinking or indecision\"}]},\"2\":{\"question\":\"How would you describe your current emotional state?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Extremely stressed or overwhelmed\"},{\"option\":\"Often restless or constantly worried\"},{\"option\":\"Feeling sad or hopeless\"},{\"option\":\"Frequently angry or irritable\"}]},\"3\":{\"question\":\"How often do you experience feelings of anxiety or worry?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Almost every day\"}]},\"4\":{\"question\":\"Have you experienced any major life changes recently? (Select all that apply)\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Divorce and Breakup\"},{\"option\":\"Relationship or family related conflicts\"}]},\"5\":{\"question\":\"How do you usually cope with stress or negative emotions?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Talking to someone I trust\"}]},\"6\":{\"question\":\"Do you struggle with negative thoughts about yourself or your abilities?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Occasionally, but I can usually manage\"}]},\"7\":{\"question\":\"How would you rate your current level of motivation and energy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Very low (I often feel drained or exhausted)\"}]},\"8\":{\"question\":\"Do you have difficulty with any of the following? (Select all that apply)\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Sleeping (falling asleep, staying asleep, etc.)\"},{\"option\":\"Eating (loss of appetite, overeating, etc.)\"},{\"option\":\"Focusing or concentrating\"},{\"option\":\"Maintaining healthy relationships\"},{\"option\":\"Managing anger or frustration\"},{\"option\":\"Making decisions\"}]},\"9\":{\"question\":\"Are there any past experiences or difficult memories you feel are affecting your mental health?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Yes, significant trauma or abuse in my past\"}]},\"10\":{\"question\":\"How do you feel about therapy? (Select all that apply)\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"I’m open to different types of therapy\"},{\"option\":\"I’m unsure about what type of therapy would help me best\"}]},\"11\":{\"question\":\"Are you currently experiencing any of the following physical symptoms related to your emotional state? (Select all that apply)\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Sleep disturbances (e.g., insomnia or excessive sleep)\"},{\"option\":\"Fatigue or low energy\"}]},\"12\":{\"question\":\"Do you often struggle with focus or concentration?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Sometimes, especially when stressed\"}]},\"13\":{\"question\":\"How would you describe your overall mental well-being?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"I feel consistently low or overwhelmed\"}]},\"14\":{\"question\":\"Do you have any previous experience with therapy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"No, this would be my first time seeking therapy\"}]}}', NULL, 0, '2025-03-07 13:51:43', '2025-03-07 13:51:43'),
(881, 10902, 19, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2025-03-13', '9:00pm-9:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/rzd-vzcf-dff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'cancel', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', 'null', 'Camera was of during the session\r\nDemographic details: 19 years old girl from Andhra Pradesh. Medical student (3rd year), lives in a hostel in triple sharing, lives in a nuclear family, timings of classes: 9 am to 4 pm. \r\nChief compalints: Depressive symptoms, low self confidence and self esteem, difficulty with analysis and identifying challenges around, trust issues and interpersonal conflicts with friends and roommates, pressure related to studies and career. \r\nAssessments: PHQ-9 (Average)\r\nGoals: Management of lower feelings, management of daily routine and boosting self-esteem. \r\nInterventions Shared: Brain dump, 5-minute action plan including self soothing activities, 54321 technique, strength based technique and positive affirmations. ', NULL, NULL, 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, 'Therapy not rescheduled', 1, '2025-03-13', 1, 29, NULL, 3, 0, '2025-03-13 14:44:51', '2025-03-13 14:44:51'),
(896, 441, 19, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', '1', '1', '4', NULL, '2', 0, '2025-03-27', '4:00pm-4:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/xce-cdhr-hij ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'agree', 'agree', 'Demographic Details: 19 years old living in Andhra Pradesh, medical student (3rd year), lives in a hostel in triple sharing. Has a nuclear family (mother and younger sister), timings of college: 9 am to 4 pm. \r\nChief complaints: frequent low feelings and mood, frequent irritability, low self-esteem and confidence, lack of time management, lack of motivation, difficulty setting boundaries and studies/career related burden. \r\nAssessment: PHQ-9 (average level)\r\nGoals: time management, management of low feelings, boosting self-esteem and strength based activity. \r\nInterventions shared: 5-minute action plan, self soothing activities, 54321 technique, distraction techniques, brain dump, listing personal strengths and achievements, positive affirmations. ', NULL, NULL, 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 4, '{\"1\":{\"question\":\"How often do you get feelings of hopelessness or emptiness?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Constantly\"}]},\"2\":{\"question\":\"How comfortable are you in expressing yourself?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Somewhat comfortable\"}]},\"3\":{\"question\":\"Do you find it hard to accept compliments?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Neutral\"}]},\"4\":{\"question\":\"How often do you compare yourself to others?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Almost always\"}]},\"5\":{\"question\":\"What would you like to improve about yourself?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"All of the above\"}]},\"6\":{\"question\":\"How well do you handle criticism?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Poorly\"}]},\"7\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel anxious in social situations?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Often\"}]},\"8\":{\"question\":\"Do you feel your self-esteem affects your daily life?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Yes, significantly\"}]},\"9\":{\"question\":\"How would you describe your self-worth?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"High\"}]},\"10\":{\"question\":\"Are you open to learning new techniques to boost your self-esteem?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Somewhat open\"}]}}', 0, 0, '2025-03-22 20:40:01', '2025-03-22 20:40:01'),
(902, 10907, 32, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', '', '', '', NULL, '', 0, '2025-03-24', '9:00pm-9:45pm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'therapy_pending', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 2, '', NULL, 0, '2025-03-24 11:11:59', '2025-03-24 11:11:59'),
(903, 10910, 31, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', '4', '3', '3', NULL, '4', 0, '2025-03-29', '12:00pm-12:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/ugd-ndyi-ewc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'agree', 'agree', 'History Of Patient Illness Demographic Details Name: Raja Marimuthu Age: 22 Years Gender: Male Occupation: Marketing Retention Office Timings: -10am-6pm Address: Mumbai Marital Status: Single Preferred Language: Tamil, But Likely Proficient In Other Languages Family Type: Single Mom And Himself Chief Complaints Feels Undervalued And Disrespected By Manager And Founder At His Current Workplace. Avoids Social Interaction At Work, Leading To Feelings Of Isolation And Sadness. Experiences Reduced Work Productivity And Lacks Motivation. Difficulty Expressing Affection Through Gifting Due To A Negative Experience At Work. \r\n● Presenting Complaints Inferiority Complex Due To Long-standing Experiences Of Bias Based On Language, Color, And Ethnicity. Feels Judged And Left Out At The Workplace After A Misunderstanding With A Senior. Decreased Enthusiasm And Engagement In Work. Emotional Discomfort Around Expressing Affection Even Towards Loved Ones, Including His Mother. \r\n● History Of Present Condition Has Been Working For 4 Years, Changed 3 Companies, And Joined His Current Company, MyMuse, In January 2025. Initially Tried To Express Appreciation By Gifting His Senior A Cadbury Chocolate, But This Was Misinterpreted, Leading To An HR Report. This Incident Led Him To Withdraw Socially At Work And Experience Emotional Distress, Impacting His Work And Personal Relationships. \r\n● Precipitating Factor (Triggering Event) Negative Response From A Senior Colleague To His Act Of Giving A Gift, Which Resulted In An HR Complaint. \r\n● Psychiatric History No Previous Psychiatric Diagnosis Or Therapy Mentioned. \r\n● Medical History No Known Medical Conditions Reported. \r\n● Medications (if Any) None Reported. \r\n● Family Medical History No Relevant Medical History Mentioned. \r\n● Physiological Ailments None Reported. \r\n● Behavioral Functioning Energy Levels: Decreased, Feels Demotivated. Appetite: No Issues Mentioned. Mood: Low, Feelings Of Sadness And Inferiority. Substance Use: No Mention Of Substance Use. Sleeping Patterns: No Disruptions Mentioned. \r\n● Work Life Currently Employed At MyMuse Since January 2025. Feels Undervalued And Experiences Negative Treatment From Management. Avoids Interacting With Colleagues Due To Fear Of Judgment. \r\n● Work-Life Balance Appears Imbalanced Due To Emotional Stress Affecting Both Work And Personal Life. \r\n● Major Stressors Feeling Judged And Undervalued At Work. Misunderstanding And Social Isolation After HR Incident. Difficulty Expressing Affection Due To Fear Of Negative Responses. ● Social Life Limited Interaction At Work. Emotional Withdrawal Due To Fear Of Judgment. Feels Disconnected Even From Close Relationships. \r\n● Daily Routine Not Explicitly Mentioned, But Seems Routine Includes Work With Little To No Social Interaction. \r\n● Client’s Perspective On The Situation Feels Undervalued And Isolated At Work. Experiences Emotional Distress After The Incident And Avoids Social Connections. Sees A Decline In His Motivation And Productivity. \r\n● Ongoing Thoughts Feels Judged And Misunderstood. Believes His Acts Of Kindness Or Affection May Be Misinterpreted. Fear Of Negative Consequences When Expressing Appreciation. \r\n● Suicidal Ideation (if Any) No Indication Of Suicidal Ideation Mentioned. \r\n● Goals Of The Current Session Build Self-confidence And Overcome The Inferiority Complex. Develop Strategies To Manage Workplace Stress And Negative Perceptions. Rebuild Trust In Expressing Affection Appropriately. Improve Work Productivity And Engagement. \r\n● Intervention Planned Affirmations: Practice Positive Affirmations Every Morning To Improve Self-worth And Confidence. Cognitive Focus: Consciously Focus Only On Work While Ignoring Negative Thoughts About The Environment. Reading Assignment: Suggested “Man\'s Search For Meaning” By Viktor Frankl To Gain Insights On Resilience And Purpose.\r\n\r\n', NULL, NULL, 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, 'No Show', 1, '2025-03-25', 0, 19, '{\"1\":{\"question\":\"What is the primary reason you are seeking support in the workplace?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Enhancing workplace relationships\"}]},\"2\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel stressed at work?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Occasionally\"}]},\"3\":{\"question\":\"How would you rate your work-life balance?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Good\"}]},\"4\":{\"question\":\"Do you feel supported by your employer regarding mental health?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Somewhat supported\"}]},\"5\":{\"question\":\"How often do you experience feelings of burnout?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Occasionally\"}]},\"6\":{\"question\":\"How comfortable are you with setting boundaries at work?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Somewhat comfortable\"}]},\"7\":{\"question\":\"How does workplace stress impact your personal life?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Moderate impact\"}]},\"8\":{\"question\":\"What is your primary goal for corporate wellness support?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Improving productivity\"}]},\"9\":{\"question\":\"How often do you take breaks during the workday?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Occasionally\"}]},\"10\":{\"question\":\"Are you interested in learning techniques to reduce workplace stress?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Somewhat interested\"}]}}', NULL, 0, '2025-03-24 14:50:39', '2025-03-27 04:28:45'),
(907, 10915, 31, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', '3', '3', '2', NULL, '5', 0, '2025-03-28', '1:00pm-1:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/ayj-wngr-npd ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'agree', 'agree', 'History of Patient Illness\r\nDemographic Details\r\nName: Saumya Mehta\r\n\r\nAge: 22 years\r\n\r\nGender: Female\r\n\r\nOccupation: Works in a startup in marketing (remote work setting)\r\n\r\nOffice Timings: Unable to work more than 2 hours a day currently\r\n\r\nAddress: Not provided\r\n\r\nMarital Status: In a relationship for 7 years (since Grade 9)\r\n\r\nPreferred Language: English, hindi\r\n\r\nFamily Type: Joint family, living with 10 members currently (previously lived with 17 members)\r\n\r\n● Chief Complaints\r\nDepression and anxiety\r\n\r\nSelf-harm (nail pricking, fidgeting, hair pulling, slapping herself)\r\n\r\nBinge eating, leading to body image issues\r\n\r\n● Presenting Complaints\r\nUnable to work for more than 2 hours a day\r\n\r\nWants to improve work duration and follow therapeutic activities\r\n\r\nStruggles with self-regulation and emotional management\r\n\r\n● History of Present Condition\r\nEpisodes of anxiety and depression began one year after her cousin brother (diagnosed with schizophrenia and psychosis) committed suicide when she was in Grade 7.\r\n\r\nHistory of aggressive behavior from her mother, including physical abuse of her and her sister during childhood.\r\n\r\n● Precipitating Factor (Triggering Event, if any)\r\nCousin brother’s suicide during Grade 7, followed by the onset of anxiety and depression.\r\n\r\n● Psychiatric History\r\nReceived therapy from July 2024 to January 2025 but did not follow the activities suggested by the therapist.\r\n\r\n● Medical History\r\nNo specific medical history provided.\r\n\r\n● Medications (if any)\r\nNo medications mentioned.\r\n\r\n● Family Medical History\r\nCousin brother diagnosed with schizophrenia and psychosis.\r\nSister is diagnosed with bipolar\r\n\r\n● Physiological Ailments\r\nBody image concerns due to being overweight.\r\n\r\n● Behavioral Functioning\r\nEnergy Levels: Low, unable to work beyond 2 hours a day.\r\n\r\nAppetite: Increased, engages in binge eating.\r\n\r\nMood: Depressive, sad and anxious mood patterns.\r\n\r\nSubstance Use: None mentioned.\r\n\r\nSleeping Patterns: not fixed pattern.\r\n\r\n● Work Life\r\nRemote work in a startup, struggling with maintaining focus and productivity.\r\n\r\n● Work-Life Balance\r\nPoor balance due to emotional exhaustion and inability to sustain work for more than 2 hours a day.\r\n\r\n● Major Stressors\r\nHistory of childhood abuse\r\n\r\nEmotional trauma following cousin’s suicide\r\n\r\nInability to manage work and personal life effectively\r\n\r\n● Social Life\r\nClose relationship with her boyfriend of 7 years, described as “pretty good.”\r\n\r\nLimited information on friendships or other social relationships.\r\n\r\n● Daily Routine\r\nNo structured routine due to low productivity and emotional distress.\r\n\r\n● Client’s Perspective on the Situation\r\nAcknowledges her inability to maintain a work schedule.\r\n\r\nWants to improve her productivity and emotional regulation.\r\n\r\nOpen to trying new strategies but struggles with follow-through.\r\n\r\n● Ongoing Thoughts\r\nSelf-critical thoughts related to body image and productivity.\r\n\r\nEmotional turmoil around family dynamics and past trauma.\r\n\r\n● Suicidal Ideation (if any)\r\nNo mention of active suicidal ideation, but history of self-harm is present.\r\n\r\n● Goals of the Current Session\r\nPractice 5-4-3-2-1 Grounding Technique 3 times a day (after waking up, before sitting to work, and before sleeping).\r\n\r\nDance for 10 minutes in the morning as a positive emotional outlet.\r\n\r\nReplace binge eating with a healthier alternative (like a sandwich) every other day.\r\n\r\nIncrease work duration to 3 hours per day gradually.\r\n\r\n● Intervention Planned\r\nGrounding Technique: Daily practice to regulate anxiety.\r\n\r\nPhysical Activity: 10-minute morning dance to improve mood and energy.\r\n\r\nNutritional Changes: Substitution of binge eating with healthier alternatives on alternate days.\r\n\r\nWork Expansion Plan: Gradual increase of work time to 3 hours daily.', '2025-04-16', '1) Talk and give techniques to tackle with Body Image Issues\n2) To suggest an another alternative when there\'s and urge to self harm\n3) Dive into the past history of mental and physical abuse that were experienced during childhood', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, 'Slot not available, can reschedule it for tonight or tomorrow ', 1, NULL, 1, 3, '{\"1\":{\"question\":\"How often do you get feelings of hopelessness or emptiness?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Often\"}]},\"2\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel like you are losing interest in activities you once enjoyed?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Often\"}]},\"3\":{\"question\":\"Do you experience fatigue even after enough sleep?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Constantly\"}]},\"4\":{\"question\":\"How well do you manage daily responsibilities?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Poorly\"}]},\"5\":{\"question\":\"Do you struggle with feelings of guilt or worthlessness?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Sometimes\"}]},\"6\":{\"question\":\"How has your appetite been affected by your mood since the last month?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Increased\"}]},\"7\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel restless or slowed down?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Constantly\"}]},\"8\":{\"question\":\"Do you have a support system you can rely on?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Yes, fully supported\"}]},\"9\":{\"question\":\"What are your primary goals for therapy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"All of the above\"}]},\"10\":{\"question\":\"How hopeful are you about your journey of recovery?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Very hopeful\"}]}}', NULL, 0, '2025-03-26 12:02:17', '2025-03-26 12:02:17'),
(908, 10899, 19, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '2025-03-27', '7:00pm-7:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/ksd-ctui-tbn ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'completed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', 'null', 'Follow up on the previous goals: Followed for a week, but could not practice after that. \r\nPresenting complaints: suicide ideation, evident signs of relapse related to contacting the partner, feelings of guilt and regret, emotional overhwhelmingness. \r\nRisk assessment done: Based on SIS evaluation was done and then a safety plan was discussed with the client in order to rule out the risk. \r\nInterventions discussed: SBSP, TIPP and self-soothing techniques, Journaling/expression related to thought restructuring. ', '2025-04-01', '1. Follow up on the previous goals. \r\n2. Practicing Self-compassion.\r\n3. Focusing on Self. ', 'psy_shortnote', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 28, NULL, 0, 0, '2025-03-27 10:18:15', '2025-03-27 10:18:15'),
(910, 10919, 31, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', '2', '3', '3', NULL, '2', 0, '2025-04-05', '9:00pm-9:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/rxq-xqry-hag', 'Maheshwari was very sweet, understanding and made time to listen to every single thing and asked the correct questions. Very mindful of what the other person would be feeling and the best part is she gave her extra 15 mins to let me talk and listen to it carefully without hurrying through to end the appointment.Loved the experience.', 'NA', 'Yes', '4', '4', '5', '4', 'completed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'agree', 'agree', 'Demographic Details\r\nName: Swathi Vijaykumar\r\n\r\nAge: 29\r\n\r\nGender: Female\r\n\r\nOccupation: Working professional \r\nOffice timings: 9-6:30\r\nAddress: Mumbai\r\n\r\nMarital status: In a relationship (unmarried)\r\n\r\nPreferred language: english, hindi\r\n\r\nFamily Type: Nuclear\r\n\r\n● Chief Complaints\r\nPersistent sadness\r\n\r\nAnxiety\r\n\r\nFeeling overwhelmed by responsibilities\r\n\r\nLow self-worth\r\n\r\nAvoidance of family interaction\r\n\r\nFeeling unheard and unappreciated\r\n\r\nSensitivity to comments about her body weight\r\n\r\n● Presenting Complaints\r\nEmotional exhaustion\r\n\r\nLack of motivation\r\n\r\nSymptoms of depression and anxiety\r\n\r\nSocial withdrawal at home\r\n\r\nNegative self-image\r\n\r\nPhysical symptoms: shortness of breath during emotional distress\r\n\r\nInconsistent eating and sleeping habits\r\n\r\n● History of Present Condition\r\nDiagnosed with depression and anxiety a year ago\r\n\r\nTook medication for a short period but discontinued due to financial constraints\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n● Precipitating Factor (Triggering event, if any)\r\nEpisode on her last birthday when a friend visited her, leading to sleeplessness, anxiety, and sadness\r\n\r\nOngoing emotional abuse and criticism from family\r\n\r\n● Psychiatric History\r\nDepression and anxiety diagnosed a year ago\r\n\r\nNo history of psychiatric hospitalization or therapy before that\r\n\r\n● Medical History\r\nNo significant medical illnesses reported\r\n\r\n● Medications (if any)\r\nPreviously prescribed antidepressants, discontinued after 1–2 weeks\r\n\r\n● Family Medical History\r\nFather with history of alcohol use\r\n\r\nNo other known psychiatric illnesses in family\r\n\r\n● Physiological Ailments\r\nLow weight (46 kg at 5’7”), may indicate nutritional deficiencies or disordered eating patterns\r\n\r\nShortness of breath during emotional episodes\r\n\r\n● Behavioral Functioning\r\nEnergy Levels: Low, especially at home\r\n\r\nAppetite: Eats a lot outside; avoids eating at home\r\n\r\nMood: Persistently low; feels anxious, overwhelmed, and underappreciated\r\n\r\nSubstance Use: None reported\r\n\r\nSleeping Patterns: Disturbed sleep, particularly during emotional triggers\r\n\r\n● Work Life\r\nTries to maintain a composed and put-together appearance at work\r\n\r\nUses work as a space to prove self-worth and escape home stress\r\n\r\n● Work - Life Balance\r\nStruggles with maintaining balance\r\n\r\nWork may provide some emotional relief, but family stress dominates overall well-being\r\n\r\n● Major Stressors\r\nFinancial burden\r\n\r\nResponsibility as the sole earner and single child\r\n\r\nLack of emotional support and recognition from family\r\n\r\nBody-shaming and emotional invalidation by parents\r\n\r\n● Social Life\r\nIntroverted but makes an effort to communicate for others’ comfort\r\n\r\nSupportive boyfriend, but internalized fear of inadequacy in relationship\r\n\r\n● Daily Routine\r\nLikely structured around work; avoids engaging at home\r\n\r\nPrefers isolating during free time (e.g., birthdays spent alone in a hotel)\r\n\r\n● Client’s Perspective on the Situation\r\nFeels unloved, unappreciated, and burdened\r\n\r\nViews home as a space of stress rather than comfort\r\n\r\nFeels unheard and emotionally dismissed by close ones\r\n\r\n● Ongoing Thoughts\r\n“I am not enough”\r\n\r\n“They don’t see my efforts”\r\n\r\n\r\nFeelings of hopelessness and sadness\r\n\r\n● Suicidal Ideation (if any)\r\nno\r\n\r\n● Goals of the Current Session\r\nBegin emotional healing through creative expression and self-compassion\r\n\r\nReconnect with inner child through letter writing\r\n\r\nEncourage healthy coping mechanisms like home workouts\r\n\r\nBuild emotional awareness through art therapy (paintings + emotional reflection)\r\n\r\n● Intervention Planned\r\nDaily home workouts\r\n\r\nLetter to childhood self\r\n\r\nComplete 3 paintings in 15 days with a reflection of 5 emotions felt post each artwork\r\n\r\nEmotional validation and insight development through therapy\r\n\r\nStrengthen internal coping mechanisms and reduce external validation dependency', '2025-05-08', '\r\nPractice communication strategies around trauma disclosure.\r\n\r\nReview and discuss emotional themes emerging from mood tracking and artwork.\r\n\r\nIntroduce grounding techniques to manage emotional overwhelm.\r\n\r\nFurther explore redefining self-worth based on internal strengths rather than external achievements.', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 3, '{\"1\":{\"question\":\"How often do you get feelings of hopelessness or emptiness?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Often\"}]},\"2\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel like you are losing interest in activities you once enjoyed?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Often\"}]},\"3\":{\"question\":\"Do you experience fatigue even after enough sleep?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Often\"},{\"option\":\"Constantly\"}]},\"4\":{\"question\":\"How well do you manage daily responsibilities?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Moderately\"}]},\"5\":{\"question\":\"Do you struggle with feelings of guilt or worthlessness?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Sometimes\"}]},\"6\":{\"question\":\"How has your appetite been affected by your mood since the last month?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Fluctuates\"}]},\"7\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel restless or slowed down?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Often\"}]},\"8\":{\"question\":\"Do you have a support system you can rely on?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Somewhat supported\"}]},\"9\":{\"question\":\"What are your primary goals for therapy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Mood stabilization\"},{\"option\":\"Better motivation\"},{\"option\":\"Improved self-worth\"},{\"option\":\"All of the above\"}]},\"10\":{\"question\":\"How hopeful are you about your journey of recovery?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Very hopeful\"}]}}', NULL, 1, '2025-04-04 15:30:07', '2025-05-07 09:11:41'),
(914, 10922, 19, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', NULL, NULL, 'null', '3', '4', '1', NULL, '4', 0, '2025-04-12', '1:00pm-1:45pm', 'https://meet.google.com/hht-zuau-xnp ', 'It was great and helpful', 'No request ', 'Yes', '4', '3', '5', '2', 'completed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'null', 'null', NULL, NULL, 'agree', 'agree', 'Demographic details: 24 years old, lives in Bhopal. Business development Manager (1.5 years), lives with her mother and daughter, father passed away when she was 6 years old due to an accident. \r\nChief Complaints: Frequent irritation, Forgetfulness, Low feelings and mood, overthinking, difficulty setting boundaries.\r\nPresenting Complaints: Feels her family has an inclination towards the younger sister, burden of responsibilities, emotional fatigue, feelings of lonliness as boyfriend and best friend shifted out of town, unresolved grief related to the loss of father at an early stage of life. \r\nGoals: Building a daily routine, Managing overthinking, anxiety management and thought restructuring. \r\nIntervention suggested: Box breathing, Distraction techniques, slee hygiene Brain dump, journaling (thought and gratitude), progressive muscle relaxation and positive affirmations. ', '2025-04-28', 'Goals for our next session are as follows:\r\n\r\n1. Learnign to set boundaries\r\n2. Digging deeper into thought analysis \r\n3. Building a softer relationship with self ', 'psy_shortnote', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 1, '{\"1\":{\"question\":\"What is your primary reason for seeking therapy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"StressRelationship issues\"},{\"option\":\"Work-related challenges\"},{\"option\":\"Personal growth\"},{\"option\":\"Any other\",\"input\":\"I\'m so quickly angered and most of my day I\'m irritated\"}]},\"2\":{\"question\":\"How often do you experience feelings of sadness or loneliness?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Often\"}]},\"3\":{\"question\":\"How comfortable are you with sharing personal experiences?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Neutral\"}]},\"4\":{\"question\":\"Do you feel supported by your friends and family?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Rarely supported\"}]},\"5\":{\"question\":\"What is your biggest source of stress?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Family\"},{\"option\":\"Relationships\"}]},\"6\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel overwhelmed by responsibilities?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Often\"}]},\"7\":{\"question\":\"How would you describe your self-esteem?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Low\"}]},\"8\":{\"question\":\"How often do you feel unmotivated or lacking energy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Almost always\"}]},\"9\":{\"question\":\"How well do you handle setbacks?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Poorly\"}]},\"10\":{\"question\":\"Are you open to exploring your past experiences in therapy?\",\"options\":[{\"option\":\"Very open\"}]}}', NULL, 0, '2025-04-11 16:04:19', '2025-04-11 16:04:19'),
